<item>
            <title>[JDK-8342958] Use jvmArgs consistently in microbenchmarks</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8342958</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Currently in the OpenJDK corpus of JMH microbenchmarks all different @Fork(jvmArgs/-Append/-Prepend = ) options are used.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
143 uses of jvmArgsAppend &lt;br/&gt;
59 uses of jvmArgsPrepend&lt;br/&gt;
18 uses of jvmArgs&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This makes for some surprises and makes it easy to override configured flags when setting up and running chunks of microbenchmarks.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I propose we consolidate on @Fork(jvmArgs = ..) as the preferred option in microbenchmarks, leaving `-jvmArgsAppend` and `-jvmArgsPrepend` free for use by ops.</description>
